											"__type" : "uid",
											"uidString" : "GD5jZV1ZSs2ob11n0paxrQ=="
										},
										"paragraphStyle" : {
											"__type" : "textStyle"
										},
										"string" : "Actually we don't want to see an array of Dictionaries but a list of repositories, so let's introduce a new domain entity. We update the “repos” method to return not a dictionary, but a Repository object that wraps the raw data. As before, we apply the fixits to create the new MyRepository class, add the rawData slot and add the setter. Now if we go back to the Repositories view and refresh it, we see the view has changed."
									},
